cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object parsing, keypoint localization, and instance segmentation, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. Additionally, the paper focuses on 3D object parsing, which involves reasoning about the spatial relationships between objects, making it relevant to robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a deep learning architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses synthetic data to train the network, which involves computer graphics (cs.GR).
